comments.body:
not necessarily recommending it, just thought I'll mention that adding an `std::map` here instead could theoretically be simpler *and* faster.
We wouldn't need expensive (double) hashing or a separate `SourceLocationEqual`, just a friendly:
```C++
struct SourceLocationLess
{
    constexpr bool operator()(const std::source_location& a, const std::source_location& b) const noexcept
    {
        return std::tuple{std::string_view{a.file_name()}, a.line(), a.column()} < std::tuple{std::string_view{b.file_name()}, b.line(), b.column()};
    }
};
```

